
# Editor and IDE state
.idea/
.vscode/

# Runtime output — the diagnostics file logger writes here (main.go)
logs/

# Local developer environment. Holds real credentials — an AIOStreams manifest
# URL embeds an encrypted debrid config blob, so this must never be committed.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Process ids recorded by scripts/dev.ps1 so it can stop what it started.
.dev-pids
.tmp/

# A Go workspace is a local-development artifact, never a committed one: it
# names absolute paths that are true on one machine. The dev stack's local
# overlay writes one outside the bind mount for exactly this reason.
go.work
go.work.sum

# Release build output (workflow-produced, never committed)
/dist/

# Private signing keys — the private half must NEVER be committed (public repo).
# The .pub public key does not match this pattern and is committed deliberately.
*.key
